Tentacle Whip.description: An elastic tentacle that lashes out at enemies from afar. It's still alive and wiggling in your hand.

Terra Trilobite.description: The mutated offspring of its extinct ancestor. Its brown shell had adapted to withstand extreme pressure.

Thin Glass Wall.description: A thin wall made from glass, perfect to create enclosures.

Thorn Wood.description: A brambly variant of the common root wood.

Throwing Daggers.description: A set of curved blades. They're evenly balanced so that throwing them is as easy as pointing a finger.

Thumper.description: A strange apparatus that sends shockwaves deep into the ground. Using it at the right spot may awaken something from its slumber. Is consumed on successful use.

Tilted Grave.description: An empty grave that has been moved out of its alignment in search for valuables.

Timeless Hourglass.description: An intact hourglass, filled with blue sand. It is not clear what period of time it measures, as the sand seems to fall incredibly slowly.

Tin Anvil.description: A better anvil for creating gear and weapons more suited for survival.

Tin Axe.description: A slower but more damaging weapon against multiple enemies.

Tin Bar.description: A tough metal ingot for blacksmithing.

Tin Dagger.description: A small blade that allows for quick stabs.

Tin Fishing Rod.description: A durable tool for pulling up bigger fish.

Tin Hoe.description: A durable tool to prepare ground for farming. Covers an area of 3x3 tiles.

Tin Pickaxe.description: A durable tool, good for breaking down walls more easily.

Tin Shovel.description: A durable shovel, well-suited for digging up ground.

Tin Sledge Hammer.description: A bulky weapon for smashing foes and walls.

Tin Sword.description: A sharp weapon for slaying foes.

Tin Workbench.description: A better workbench to prepare you for the underground world.

Tome of the Dead.description: A vile treatise on the conjuring of dark spirits.

equip.secondary: Use: Summons a melee skeleton minion.

Tome of the Deep.description: Powerful incantions barely utterable by the human tongue.

equip.secondary: Use: Summons an orbiting jellyfish minion dealing damage on impact.

Tome of the Dark.description: More of a pamphlet, beginners guide to shadowmancy.

equip.secondary: Use: Summons a ranged bat minion.

Topaz Ring.description: A precious little ring with a yellow gemstone on top.

Torch.description: Light up your surroundings. Can also be placed on the ground and attached to walls.

Torc Necklace.description: A piece of jewelry for the neck that's merely a hoop with a gap. Worn by many different cultures throughout world history.

Tornis Kingfish.description: An extremely rare enigma of sea life that seems to unify all other fish beneath it.

Towel.description: A towel is about the most massively useful thing an underground miner can have.

Tower Shell Necklace.description: A necklace featuring a coiling shell. Its ever turning spiral structure is captivating.

Trenchcoat.description: A coat with deep pockets fit for a hoggish, dodgy fancier.

Triangle Trinket.description: A strange gold piece vibrating with energy.

Trinity Heart.description: A symbiosis of an ancient gemstone with organic matter, resulting in a physically impossible material. It pulsates in energetic rhythms of three, a celestial pattern that must have been of utter importance to a spacefaring species.

Triops Fossil.description: The petrified remains of a species that still exists to this day, even after 220 million years.

Kelple Hatchling.description: A young that comes up from the ground once it had enough time to slumber in the dark. Its shell is still blank but in time it will be populated by the kelp that it feeds on.

Kelple.description: A marine reptile and natural gardener, that chews down on kelp when it grows too plenty. It doesn't need many nutrients, so whatever it eats comes out again in a condensed ball shape that is free for the taking.

Turtle Shell.description: A hard shell that once belonged to a graceful sea creature. You feel much more protected when holding it.

Twisted Agate.description: A green gem shaped like a spiral.

Unleashed Core Commander Figurine.description: A lifelike representation of the Unleashed Core Commander.

Desert King Chest.description: An intricate, unique chest with a purple gemstone locked in its center.

Desert Prince Chest.description: An intricate, unique chest with an orange gemstone locked in its center.

Desert Queen Chest.description: An intricate, unique chest with a green gemstone locked in its center.

Unusual Potion.description: A two-component potion that is risky to drink.

Upgrade Station.description: A high-tech workbench to upgrade tools and weapons, making them stronger and more effective.

Valentine's Candles.description: A handful of small, pink candles that fill the air with a whiff of vanille.

Valentine's Chest.description: This heart-themed chest is great to tuck away little trinkets of love.

Rose Petal Flooring.description: This little paper bag contains enough rose petals to cover a 1x1 floor tile with them. Great to lay out a path of love.

Love Letter.description: A scented letter that contains words of love and appreciation. Give it to someone in dire need of affection.

Valentine Necklace.description: A golden necklace featuring a big, shiny heart. You feel something you can't describe, when wearing it so close to your own.

effects: 3 set: +100% longer duration of applied charm effects

Heart Painting.description: A simple painting showing nothing more than a heart. Sometimes this is all one needs in these dark times.

Caveling Brute Plushie.description: A big plushie, resembling a caveling brute holding a heart. Even those need a little bit of love sometimes.

Valentine's Gift.description: This rose and silver-colored gift is packed with a variety of different charming items.

Valentine Ring.description: A golden ring featuring a candy-colored heart. The perfect gift to give to someone you like.

effects: 3 set: +100% longer duration of applied charm effects

Heart-shaped Rug.description: Nothing speaks "love" like a big fuzzy heart on the floor. It smells like wool and lavender.

Wall Hearts.description: An assortment of hearts cut from paper, they look great on walls and make a base just a little bit more lovely.

Valentine Crafting Table.description: A workbench containing tools and blueprints to create some beautiful decorative items.

Dracularva Cape.description: A black satin cape fit for a vampire. The crimson flip-up collar adds to the evil look.

Vampire Eel.description: A bloodsucking fish latching onto everything that has a pulse.

regular: +3 life on melee hit for 10 min
rare: +4 life on melee hit for 10 min
epic: +4 life on melee hit for 10 min

Broken Vending Machine.description: A broken automaton that once contained snacks and other goods. It looks like it was forced open.

Vending Machine.description: An old, still functioning automaton that is proof of advanced technology and a sophisticated society.

Verdant Dragonfish.description: This draconic fish has green scales that can withstand remarkably high temperatures.

Vicious Ring.description: The unsettling gaze of this ring causes minions to stay on high alert.

Void Gun.description: A particle weapon with unknown inner workings. It emits balls of void that distort spacetime to inflict high damage.

Alien Tech Block.description: A mysterious intricate piece of architecture.

Glass Wall.description: A solid wall made from glass. Works well for building a base or enclosures.

Paintable Wall.description: A bleak stone wall ready to be turned lively with colors.

conditions: Immune to being slowed by slime

Urschleims Chest.description: A large chest, made from the hardened mass of the gargantuan amoeba. You feel uneasy in its presence.

conditions: Immune to being slowed by slime
Immune to being slowed by slime

Urschleim Scanner.description: Scans the world for Urschleim. Consumed on successful scan.

Primeval Slime Cell.description: A highly mutative, crystalized cell. To resummon Urschleim, activate it in the Passage where ancient lifeforms still roam. Consumed in the process.

Metropolis Block.description: A sturdy piece of city architecture, decorated with glass and gold.

Clay Block.description: A red, wet piece of clay.

Crystal Block.description: A blue, glistening piece of crystal.

Dark Stone Block.description: A sturdy dark piece of stone.

Stone Bricks Wall.description: A solid wall made with interlocking blocks.

Desert Block.description: A sandy piece of desert stone.

Maze Block.description: An extremely durable block used to build ancient mazes.

Desert Temple Block.description: A sturdy piece of ancient architecture, decorated with tiles and gold.

Dirt Block.description: A brown solid piece of dirt.

Explosives Deposit.description: A highly dangerous box of explosives that can be placed like a wall. Don't hit it or it will blow up right in your face.

Galaxite Wall.description: An otherwordly wall speckled with glittering stars.

Gleam Wood Wall.description: An enigmatic wall reinforced with glimmering plates.

Grass Block.description: A lush piece of vertical plants.

Larva Hive Block.description: A lumpy… living piece of hive material.

Beach Block.description: A sandy piece of the coastal stone.

Meadow Block.description: A mellow piece of earth with little summer flowers growing on it.

Thermite Wall.description: An unstable, explosive piece of wall.

Obsidian Block.description: An indestructible piece of obsidian. You're not supposed to have this…

Fossil Block.description: Layers upon layers of living matter have been crushed into a dense, twisted mass.

Sand Block.description: A yellow fragile piece of sand.

Scarlet Wall.description: A reinforced metal wall to set up your base for tough encounters.

Snow Block.description: A white cold piece of snow.

Straw-bale Wall.description: A reinforced straw wall to set up a cozy farm.

Turf Block.description: A soft mossy piece of turf.

Wood Wall.description: A solid wall made from wood. Works well for building a base.

Wash Basin.description: A container used to store water and filling up watering cans.

Sun Kelp.description: A large seaweed that lives off of the light cast down into the wilderness.

Azeos Lily.description: A floating plant that is part of a rich aquatic ecosystem.

Water Well.description: An ancient stone well to take water from.

Ancient Waypoint.description: A miraculous gemstone device used to teleport to other waypoints and portals. When placed, it takes 10 minutes to charge up before it can be accessed.

Wedding Dress.description: A simple, white dress elevating the beauty of its wearer. There are many occasions to wear it but the most important one is being a bride.

Flower Crown.description: A beautiful crown made from leaves and pink roses. It resembles a love that feels like eternal spring.

Old Wheelbarrow.description: A broken wheelbarrow stuck in its own molten contents. It seems like it couldn't withstand the extreme heat.

White Coralotl.description: A small white amphibian with outward-protruding gills that look like corals. It also uses them to draw nutrients out of the waters of the Sunken Sea.

White Glass Ring.description: This ring is made from a milky, translucent material. The light it reflects makes it harder for enemies to hit you.

White Rose Bouquet.description: This beautiful bouquet made from white roses will elevate the look of every room. Give it to someone you like dearly.

White Whistle.description: A rare artifact made from precious, white stone. It doesn't produce a sound when you try to use it.

Winter Bell.description: This golden and white bell produces a fine ringing sound, it's faint and reminds one of falling snow.

Winter Cookies.description: Nicely decorated this handful of cookies will put one in a seasonal mood. There's even a little core-shaped one in there.
conditionsWhenConsumed: You can feel the winter embracing you for 1 min

Winter Dinner.description: A full meal to warm your belly in the cold season. Prepared with a roasted larva, hot heartberry sauce, dumplings and some greens.

Witch Doctor Vest.description: A worn vest with a simple shirt underneath.

effects: 3 set: +31.5% minion attack speed

Witch Doctor Hat.description: A rustic top hat with various trinkets along the brim.

effects: 3 set: +31.5% minion attack speed

Witch Doctor Jeans.description: A pair of jeans with a golden chain strapped on.

Wood Bow.description: A crude bow to shoot foes from afar.

Wood Chest.description: Very crude armor for the upper body. Offers minor protection.

Wood Bridge.description: Used to cross chasms and water but also makes for a nice floor.

Wood Crossbow.description: A small wooden crossbow that swiftly shoots bolts.

Wood Door.description: Close up your base with this simple door.

Wooden Ring.description: A simple wooden ring, nothing more, nothing less.

Wooden Sign \"Core\".description: Driftwood with patterns and carvings showing the Core.

Wooden Sign \"Tulip\".description: Driftwood with patterns and carvings showing a Glow Tulip.

Wooden Thorn Ring.description: A circular, brambly root with sharp thorns pointing outward.

Wood.description: A piece of giant root to create all sorts of things.

Wood Fence.description: A simple fence to protect what's rightfully yours.

Wood Fence Gate.description: A simple gate for the wooden fence.

Wood Fishing Rod.description: A crude tool for pulling up fish.

Wood Floor.description: Simple wooden slats for decorating your base.

Wood Helm.description: Slight protection for the head but you should look for better options soon.

Wooden Hoe.description: A crude tool to prepare ground for farming.

Wood Pickaxe.description: A crude tool, useful for breaking down walls.

Wood Pants.description: The next best thing when it comes to lower body armor.

Wooden Pillar.description: This decorative, wooden pillar is just the basic design for a whole lot more colorful variants.

Wooden Shield.description: A useful off-hand item to block hits from enemies.
Wooden Shield.mechanic: Shield yourself and reduce any incoming damage by 70%

Wood Shovel.description: A crude shovel, useful for digging up ground.

Wooden Spike Trap.description: A crude spike trap that only reacts to enemies.

Wood Stool.description: A simple, workable stool made from wood. A true hobbyist might turn this into something more beautiful.

Wooden Sword.description: A crude weapon to fend off foes.

Wood Table.description: A simple, workable table made from wood. A true hobbyist might turn this into something more beautiful.

Basic Workbench.description: The most basic of all workbenches.

Wool.description: An incredibly soft tuft of wool that has a pleasant scent to it.

Worker Handcuff.description: Cast from thick metal this tool seemed to be attached to a chain. Has it been used to keep the unlawful from running away?

Woven Mat.description: Groundcover made from a net of firm plants.

Woven Straw Floor.description: A reinforced floor, woven from meadow straw.

Yellow Blister Head.description: A fish with large yellow bubbles on its head.

Yellow Glowbug.description: This flying bug always appears in swarms which appear as dancing lights. Its yellow glow is biome-specific.

Yellow Kelp.description: A yellow lump of marine plants.

Zealot's Scimitar.description: A brilliant sword that channels mana into the blade to increase its power.
